# YouTube Clone Without Login System

This project is a simple YouTube clone built with React Native, allowing users to browse and watch videos without logging in.

## Features

- **Home Screen**: Displays a list of videos fetched from an API. Each video item shows a thumbnail, title, and description.
- **Infinite Scrolling**: Automatically loads more videos as the user scrolls down.
- **Loading Indicator**: Shows a loading spinner while fetching data.
- **Video Detail Screen**: Plays the selected video and displays its title and description.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js (version 14 or higher)
- npm
- Expo CLI

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository**:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/itzvp/AwesomeProject

   ```

Install dependencies:
npm install

- npm start # you can open iOS, Android, or web from here, or run them directly with the commands below.
- npm run android
- npm run ios # requires an iOS device or macOS for access to an iOS simulator
- npm run web

File Structure

├── assets
│ └── styles.js # Contains styles for the app
├── components
│ └── VideoItem.js # Component to display individual video items
├── screens
│ ├── HomeScreen.js # Home screen component
│ └── VideoDetailScreen.js # Video detail screen component
├── App.js # Main entry point of the app
├── package.json # Project metadata and dependencies
└── README.md # This file

API Endpoint
https://impactmindz.in/client/boub/back_end/api/product
